            "id": 1,
            "parent": 9,
            "text": "Infection with Mycobacterium tuberculosis remains a major cause of morbidity and mortality all over the world . <S>",
            "relation": "BACKGROUND"
        },
        {
            "id": 2,
            "parent": 3,
            "text": "Since the effectiveness of the only available tuberculosis vaccine , Mycobacterium bovis bacillus Calmette - Gu\u00e9rin ( BCG ) , is suboptimal ,",
            "relation": "CAUSE-RESULT"
        },
        {
            "id": 3,
            "parent": 1,
            "text": "there is a strong demand",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 4,
            "parent": 3,
            "text": "to develop new tuberculosis vaccines . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 5,
            "parent": 6,
            "text": "As tuberculosis is an airborne disease ,",
            "relation": "CAUSE-RESULT"
        },
        {
            "id": 6,
            "parent": 3,
            "text": "the intranasal route of vaccination might be preferable . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 7,
            "parent": 3,
            "text": "Live influenza virus vaccines might be considered as potential vectors for mucosal immunization against various viral or bacterial pathogens ,",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 8,
            "parent": 7,
            "text": "including M. tuberculosis . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 9,
            "parent": 0,
            "text": "We generated several subtypes of attenuated recombinant influenza A viruses",
            "relation": "ROOT"
        },
        {
            "id": 10,
            "parent": 9,
            "text": "expressing the 6-kDa early secretory antigenic target protein ( ESAT-6 ) of M. tuberculosis from the NS1 reading frame . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 11,
            "parent": 9,
            "text": "We were able to demonstrate the potency of influenza virus NS vectors",
            "relation": "FINDINGS"
        },
        {
            "id": 12,
            "parent": 11,
            "text": "to induce an M. tuberculosisspecific Th1 immune response in mice . <S>",
            "relation": "ENABLEMENT"
        },
        {
            "id": 13,
            "parent": 11,
            "text": "Moreover , intranasal immunization of mice and guinea pigs with such vectors induced protection against mycobacterial challenge , similar to that",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 14,
            "parent": 13,
            "text": "induced by BCG vaccination . <S> <P>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        }
    ]
